    <h2>The History and Evolution of Reginet</h2>
    <p>The Tamil Nadu Registration Department launched TNREGINET (commonly referred to as <strong>Reginet</strong> by citizens) as part of the state\'s e-governance initiative to digitize land registration services. The portal was developed to eliminate the opacity and inefficiency that characterized the manual SRO registration process before computerization. In the pre-digital era, obtaining an EC required a physical visit to the SRO, a written application, waiting for clerks to manually search voluminous physical index books, and collecting the certificate after several days. Errors in the physical index entries were common, and access to records was often controlled by intermediaries (brokers and clerks) who charged informal fees.</p>
